# Student Performance Data Analysis
This project analyzes exercise and pulse rate data using Python, Pandas, and Seaborn.

Import Libraries:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

Load Dataset:
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mwaskom/seaborn-data/master/exercise.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(url)

df.head()

Dataset Info:
df.info()
df.describe()

First Graph:
sns.countplot(x='kind', data=df)
plt.title("Exercise Type Distribution")
plt.show()

Second Graph:
sns.boxplot(x='diet', y='pulse', data=df)
plt.title("Pulse Rate by Diet Type")
plt.show()

Conclusion:
## Conclusion

- The dataset shows different distributions for exercise types.
- Pulse rate varies depending on diet and activity.
- Data visualization helps in understanding patterns clearly.
